# __GAME_TITLE__

Standalone 2D/2.5D isometric RPG built with Python and raylib through the
`pyray` API. Game rules run deterministically and can be tested without opening
a window. Playable content is installed as immutable, hash-verified runtime
bundles under `game_data/worlds/`.

## Requirements

- Python 3.11 or 3.12
- the pinned `raylib==6.0.1.0` Python distribution

## Development

```bash
python -m pip install --requirement requirements.lock
python -m pip install --no-build-isolation --no-deps -e .
python scripts/verify_game.py
ruff check src tests scripts run_game.py
ruff format --check src tests scripts run_game.py
python -m unittest discover -s tests
python scripts/native_smoke.py
python -m game --world WORLD_ID --release RELEASE_ID
```

List installed releases with `python -m game --list-worlds`. Run a selected
release without graphics with `--headless-ticks N`.

Record deterministic gameplay with `--record-replay-slot SLOT`, then verify and
reproduce it with `--replay-slot SLOT`. Replay recording always starts from a
clean initial state and cannot be combined with `--load-slot`. Playback is a
separate execution mode and cannot be combined with save, load, recording, or
headless-tick options.

The process working directory is irrelevant: application data is resolved from
the installed project, while saves and replays are written only to the explicit
user-data root outside the game tree. Replays use
`replays/WORLD_ID/RELEASE_ID/SLOT.json`; saves use the parallel `saves/` tree.
Empty or relative `XDG_DATA_HOME`/`LOCALAPPDATA` values are ignored in favor of
an absolute home-based platform default. `game_data/worlds.lock.json` is the
authority for installed releases.

## Shared game assets

World-specific processed assets stay inside immutable imported bundles. Only
presentation resources genuinely shared by the game belong under
`game_data/shared/`. After adding, replacing, or removing one, update its
attribution in `THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md`, then regenerate and verify the lock:

```bash
python scripts/lock_shared_assets.py
python scripts/verify_game.py
```

`game_data/shared.lock.json` binds every shared path, size, media type, byte
hash, and the notices file. Never edit the lock manually. It rejects unlisted
files, extension/media mismatches, symlinks, unsafe paths, and authoring,
provider, model, or workflow metadata. A missing license or provenance entry is
a release blocker even when the bytes are technically valid.

## Release checks

```bash
python scripts/benchmark_scene.py --world WORLD_ID --release RELEASE_ID
python scripts/package_game.py --output ../releases/__GAME_ID__-0.1.0.zip
```

Every package includes its runtime lock, shared-asset lock, bundle catalog,
licenses, and a deterministic file manifest. The explicit output must be outside the verified
source tree and must not already exist. It is an unpack-and-run source
artifact, not a wheel: extract it and start it with `python run_game.py` so the
locked data root remains beside `src/`. A later native packaging tool may wrap
the same verified tree as an executable. See `THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md`
before distribution.

The source ZIP includes recursive Python tests and bounded runtime-boundary-
checked `.json`, image, audio, font, and GLSL fixtures. Other test artifact types must be added
as an explicit packaging-contract change; they are never swept in implicitly.
